  "body": "Turns our that when running a container in host network, its `podStatus *kubecontainer.PodStatus` that is passed to dockertools.SyncPod() will always contain empty IP, as a result, the `PodIP` environment becomes empty.\n\nMaybe we want to use the `apiPodStatus` instead of `podStatus` in this case to [determine the pod IP](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/v1.3.0-alpha.2/pkg/kubelet/dockertools/manager.go#L1805-L1808) ? Since the apiPodStatus has the valid PodIP, which is [populated by kubelet](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/v1.3.0-alpha.2/pkg/kubelet/kubelet.go#L3271-L3278) when the container runs in host network.\n\nOr just populate the podIP with hostIP in `dockertools.syncPod` when the container runs on host network.\n\nRef https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/22666\n\ncc @aaronlevy @kubernetes/sig-node @pmorie\n",
